./.body:
Portia Workflow
Portia Workflow is a lightweight JQuery based plugin that provides some features like Workflow designer and Workflow Engine to create and run new dynamic workflows in other projects.You can find documentation and samples here

docs/designer/designer.html.title: Designer
docs/designer/designer.html.body:
Designer
Portia Workflow gives you a simple environment to design and test your custom workflows. This widget currently uses bootstrap 4.0 and also it supports bootstrap 3.0.

docs/designer/setup.html.title: Setup
docs/designer/setup.html.body:
Setup
Minimum requirements
To get started, you have to import at least 7 libraries in your page

JQeury libraryBase JQuery library


JQuery UITo add some abilities such as Drag and Drop to our designer


BootstrapPortia Workflow uses bootstrap for it's UI. It is compatible with both of the version 3.0 and 4.0. So you need to import one of them in your page.




Font-AwesomeTo have a light weight plugin, Portia Workflow uses font-awesome for it's icons


jquery-confirmIn some cases like removing an activity, Portia Workflow uses this plugin to show a confirmation or alert dialog. This plugin will remove in future.


JQuery UI Touch PunchIf you want to use Drop and Drop functionality in your touch screen devices, you should add this library

And Finally
Portia Sequence flow designer




Setting Up
The only thing you need to do is calling seqDesigner for your DOM element.



    $(document).ready(function(){
        $('#designer').seqDesigner();
    });
